\subsection{\href{https://beta.lmfdb.org/knowledge/show/group.outer_aut}{Outer automorphism group}}
\begin{definition*}\label{group.outer_aut}
\uses{group,group.automorphism,group.inner_automorphism,group.subgroup.normal}
If $G$ is a \hyperref[group]{group}, its \hyperref[group.inner_automorphism]{inner automorphism} group is a \hyperref[group.subgroup.normal]{normal subgroup} of the full \hyperref[group.automorphism]{automorphism group}.  Then, the \textbf{outer automorphism group} of $G$ is
\[ \mathrm{Out}(G) = \Aut(G)/\mathrm{Inn}(G).\]

Note that the term \textbf{outer automorphism} is often used to mean any automorphism of a group $G$ which is not an inner automorphism. In this case, the nontrivial elements of the outer automorphism group are cosets of outer automorphisms. 
\end{definition*}


